<h2 id="what-matters">What Matters for Multi-Location Payroll</h2>

Multi-location payroll is harder than single-location payroll in ways that aren't obvious until you're running it:

<ul>
  <li><strong>Multi-state tax compliance</strong> -- if your locations cross state lines, each state has different withholding rules, unemployment rates, and filing deadlines</li>
  <li><strong>Varied pay structures</strong> -- some locations may have tipped employees, others salary, others hourly with overtime</li>
  <li><strong>Centralized processing</strong> -- you need one payroll run across all locations, not separate accounts per site</li>
  <li><strong>Time tracking integration</strong> -- hours from your scheduling tool need to flow into payroll without manual entry</li>
  <li><strong>Benefits administration</strong> -- health insurance, 401(k), PTO tracking across all employees regardless of location</li>
</ul>

I've watched operators try to manage multi-location payroll with spreadsheets and a bookkeeper. It works until it doesn't -- and when it breaks, it's usually a tax compliance issue that costs far more than any payroll platform subscription.

<h2 id="gusto">Gusto -- Best for Multi-Location Small Business</h2>

Gusto is the payroll platform I recommend to every operator I work with. It handles full-service payroll -- tax calculations, filings, direct deposit, W-2s, 1099s -- plus benefits administration, HR tools, and compliance, all in one platform that a non-HR person can manage.

<h3>Why Gusto wins for operators:</h3>

<p><strong>Multi-location support.</strong> One Gusto account handles all your locations. Employees are assigned to work locations, and Gusto automatically applies the correct state and local tax rules. Add a new location in a different state and Gusto handles the registration and compliance automatically.</p>

<p><strong>Tip tracking and tipped wages.</strong> For restaurant, salon, and service business operators, Gusto calculates tip credits, tracks tipped minimum wage compliance, and handles tip reporting on tax forms. This alone saves hours per pay period compared to manual tracking.</p>

<p><strong>Time tracking integration.</strong> Gusto's built-in time tracking works, and it integrates with Homebase, When I Work, and other scheduling platforms. Hours flow directly into payroll without manual entry or CSV uploads.</p>

<p><strong>Benefits.</strong> Health insurance, 401(k), commuter benefits, and workers' comp -- all administerable through Gusto. For operators who want to offer benefits but don't have an HR department, Gusto makes it manageable.</p>

<p><strong>Automatic compliance.</strong> New hire reporting, tax form filing, year-end W-2 distribution, and state-specific compliance are all handled automatically. Gusto stays current with changing tax laws so you don't have to.</p>

