<h2 id="quickbooks">QuickBooks Payroll -- Best for QuickBooks Users</h2>

If your accounting already runs on QuickBooks, QuickBooks Payroll is the natural add-on. The integration is seamless -- payroll transactions automatically categorize in your chart of accounts, and payroll liabilities track in real-time.

<h3>Strengths:</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Accounting integration</strong> -- eliminates double-entry between payroll and books</li>
  <li><strong>Same-day direct deposit</strong> -- on Premium and Elite plans</li>
  <li><strong>1099 contractor payments</strong> -- handles contractor payroll alongside employee payroll</li>
  <li><strong>Tax penalty protection</strong> -- Intuit covers penalties for errors on Premium and Elite</li>
</ul>

<h3>Weaknesses:</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Benefits are add-on</strong> -- health insurance and 401(k) cost extra through partnerships</li>
  <li><strong>Multi-location management</strong> is less intuitive than Gusto</li>
  <li><strong>HR features are thin</strong> -- it's a payroll tool, not an HR platform</li>
  <li><strong>Pricing is opaque</strong> -- frequent promotional pricing makes true cost hard to evaluate</li>
</ul>

